Issues.Body:
It appears that the default vanilla-CSS setup does not show how to enable containers?

with` style.css`
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

and `tailwind.config.js`
```js
const defaultTheme = require('tailwindcss/defaultTheme');

/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: ['./src/**/*.{html,js}'],
  theme: {
    container: {
      center: true,
    },
    extend: {
      fontFamily: {
        sans: ['Inter var', ...defaultTheme.fontFamily.sans],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

the container classes are not applied.

The plugin attribute has to be updated to
```js
plugins: [
    require('tailwindcss-container-sizes')(),
  ],
```

but I cannot find this documented anywhere, I just found this old issue that helped me figure it out: https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/issues/446

### Issue Description:

I am working on a Nuxt.js application using Tailwind CSS and the @tailwindcss/typography package for text formatting. I attempted to customize text color and styles using a custom Tailwind CSS configuration file and the @tailwindcss/typography package. However, unfortunately, the changes are not being applied as expected.

### Steps to Reproduce the Issue:

1. Installed specific versions of packages in the `package.json` file as follows:

   ```json
   "devDependencies": {
     "@nuxt/content": "^2.7.2",
     "@nuxt/devtools": "^0.8.0",
     "@nuxtjs/tailwindcss": "^6.8.0",
     "@tailwindcss/typography": "^0.5.9",
     "@types/node": "^20.5.0",
     "nuxt": "^3.6.5"
   }
   ```

2. Modified the `tailwind.config.js` file to customize text colors as follows:

   ```javascript
   /** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
   module.exports = {
     content: [],
     theme: {
       extend: {
         colors: {
           'basic': '#023047',
           'secondary': '#8ecae6',
         },
         typography: ({ theme }) => ({
           pink: {
             css: {
               // ... (Custom style changes for text)
             },
           },
         }),
       },
     },
     plugins: [
       require('@tailwindcss/typography'),
     ],
   };
   ```

3. Applied custom classes to HTML elements in the template as follows:

   ```html
   <template>
     <section class="max-w-3xl m-auto p-10 lg:mt-10 text-basic prose pink">
       <h1 class="font-semibold text-4xl mb-6">{{ data.title }}</h1>
       <ContentDoc />
     </section>
   </template>
   ```

### Expected Behavior:

I expect the custom changes to be applied to text colors and styles according to the specified configuration.

### Actual Result:

Unfortunately, the custom changes are not being applied as expected. The colors and styles do not match the specified custom configuration.
